# WHAT IT IS
#   `bulk-did-hash` is a **single-purpose CLI for computing
#   SHA-256 hashes of AT Protocol DIDs** — used in the Bluesky
#   moderation tooling chain where SHA-256(DID) hashes are
#   exposed instead of raw `did:plc:...` or `did:web:...`
#   identifiers (because the raw DIDs in some contexts are
#   considered identifying information that benefits from
#   one-way hashing before being shared across systems —
#   e.g., labeler-to-labeler federation, moderation-action
#   audit logs that need privacy-preserving references to
#   accounts, anonymous abuse-reporting pipelines).
#
#   The tool accepts EITHER a raw `did:plc:...` /
#   `did:web:...` DID OR a Bluesky handle (`alice.bsky.social`,
#   `mozzius.dev`, `bsky.app`, any handle resolvable via the
#   `com.atproto.identity.resolveHandle` XRPC method).  When
#   given a handle, it resolves it to a DID first via the
#   `@atproto/api` library's `AtpAgent.resolveHandle({handle})`
#   typed method, hitting `https://public.api.bsky.app`'s
#   public AppView surface, and THEN hashes the resolved DID
#   with SHA-256.
#
#   Two subcommands:
#
#     sha <DID-OR-HANDLE>           Hash a single DID or handle
#                                   to stdout
#     bulk <PATH-TO-FILE.txt>       Read a newline-separated
#                                   file of DIDs/handles,
#                                   resolve each handle to its
#                                   DID, SHA-256-hash each DID,
#                                   and write the resulting
#                                   hashes (one per line) to
#                                   `./hashes.csv` in the
#                                   current working directory
#
#   Default behavior with no subcommand prints usage:
#
#     Usage: npx bulk-did-hash sha <did-or-handle>
#     Usage: npx bulk-did-hash bulk <path-to-file.txt>
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from src/index.ts +
#                       src/sha.ts + src/bulk.ts dispatcher;
#                       extracted via raw.githubusercontent.com
#                       fetch of mozzius/bulk-did-hash master
#                       src/*.ts)
#
#   bulk-did-hash <SUBCOMMAND> [ARG]
#
#   Subcommands:
#     sha <DID-OR-HANDLE>           Hash a single DID/handle.
#                                   Handle is auto-resolved via
#                                   AtpAgent.resolveHandle()
#                                   against
#                                   https://public.api.bsky.app
#     bulk <PATH-TO-FILE>           Bulk-hash from a newline-
#                                   separated input file.
#                                   Output: ./hashes.csv (one
#                                   hex SHA-256 per line)
#
#   (No global flags — index.ts is a bare `switch(arg[0])`
#    dispatcher with no global option parser; arguments after
#    the subcommand are positional.)
